    "body": "### Problem\n\nLSP intermittent failure to attach due to unstable arguments passed to cmd on Windows.\r\n\r\nI haven't looked at rpc.lua because I probably wouldn't understand it but I think there is a strange bug on Windows whereby the argument passed to some function in rpc.lua is not stable.\r\n\r\nIt seems to alternate between a path command or the mason CMD containing the literal path to the package binary.\r\n\r\nI understand this could be a Mason bug also but I don't know enough about the internals to guess which.\r\n\r\nI have been testing with ZLS but this behaviour occurs with all LSPs I have tried to install with Mason.\r\n\r\n\r\nZLS\r\n\r\nFail\r\n\r\n`[INFO][2024-03-18 15:46:43] .../vim/lsp/rpc.lua:662\t\"Starting RPC client\"\t{  args = {},  cmd = \"zls\",  extra = {    cwd = \"C:/Work/Projects/Zig/exercises\"  }}`\r\n\r\nSuccess\r\n\r\n`[INFO][2024-03-18 13:53:15] .../vim/lsp/rpc.lua:662\t\"Starting RPC client\"\t{  args = {},  cmd = \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Z\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\nvim-data\\\\mason\\\\bin\\\\zls.CMD\",  extra = {    cwd = \"C:/Work/Projects/Zig/exercises\"  }}`\r\n\r\nPassed \"cmd = {\"zls\"}\" to the lspconfig table and added the mason binary to path.\r\n\r\n`[INFO][2024-03-18 16:18:23] .../vim/lsp/rpc.lua:662\t\"Starting RPC client\"\t{  args = {},  cmd = \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Z\\\\AppData\\\\Local\\\\nvim-data\\\\mason\\\\packages\\\\zls\\\\bin\\\\zls.EXE\",  extra = {    cwd = \"C:/Work/Projects/Zig/exercises\"  }}`\r\n\r\nInstalled zls via scoop, removed cmd entry from lspconfig table.\r\n\r\n`[INFO][2024-03-18 16:26:20] .../vim/lsp/rpc.lua:662\t\"Starting RPC client\"\t{  args = {},  cmd = \"C:\\\\Users\\\\Z\\\\scoop\\\\shims\\\\zls.EXE\",  extra = {    cwd = \"C:/Work/Projects/Zig/exercises\"  }}`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nI guess you'd need to find someone with a Windows machine, get them to install any LSP with mason.nvim, configure with lspconfig and mason-lspconfig.nvim and open files a bunch of times to see the behaviour.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should be passing the correct argument, rather than dithering between the two based on the procession of Venus in the firmament.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.9.5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI have no idea, sorry\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nMicrosoft Windows NT 10.0.19045.0\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nI'm on Windows I don't know what this is, bro\n\n### Installation\n\nExecutable installer from the interweb sitepage github dot com",
