            "body": "This is either a mason/mason-lspconfig or lspconfig issue. neovim core only provides the `lsp.start` and `lsp.start_client` methods, and there the `cmd` parameter needs to be provided. Whoever is setting that, would cause this problem. I'm not familiar with mason-lspconfig so I'm not sure if it is coming from there, or from lspconfig.\r\n\r\n",
